text:
Fix this

<Input
          placeholder="https://youtube.com..."
          value={videoLink}
          onChange={(val) => setVideLink(val.target.value)}
        />
        
Here's the corrected code:

```jsx
<Input
  placeholder="https://youtube.com..."
  value={videoLink}
  onChange={(e) => setVideoLink(e.target.value)}
/>
```

The fixes made are:
1. Changed `setVideLink` to `setVideoLink` (fixed typo)
2. Changed the parameter name from `val` to `e` (event) which is more conventional
3. The event object contains the input value in `e.target.value`

This assumes you have defined the state variable `videoLink` and its setter `setVideoLink` using useState hook like this:

```jsx
const [videoLink, setVideoLink] = useState('');
```
